    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn #35998 and #33509, the `vim.lsp.protocol.Methods` enum was replaced by some type aliases (`vim.lsp.protocol.Method.{ClientToServer, ServerToClient}.{Request, Notification}`). The removal of the enum made it difficult to work with types like `lsp.HandlerContext` because [its `method` field](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/a4006360f1d43211ec9abf5b869f49e082ab82e7/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_meta.lua#L8) is annotated as a `string`, not a `vim.lsp.protocol.Method`. This means when people use it, there's no LSP information (completion, hover, etc.) for the methods.\n\nFor example, when writing a function that takes an `lsp.handlerContext` object as the parameter:\n```lua\n---@param ctx lsp.handlerContext\nfunction(ctx)\n  -- Before `vim.lsp.protocol.Methods` deprecation\n  if ctx.method == vim.lsp.protocol.Methods.textDocument_references then\n    -- users can autocomplete the method name, no need to remember the exact name or\n    -- worry about any typo, etc.\n    do_things()\n  end\n  -- After the deprecation\n  if ctx.method == \"textDocument/references\" then\n    -- because `ctx.method` is a string, we have no autocomplete whatsoever\n    -- and have to memorise and manually enter the full method\n    do_things()\n  end\nend\n```\n\nFrom a simple grep in the repo, I've also noticed `method` field being labelled as `string` in `runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_meta/protocol.lua` ([here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/a4006360f1d43211ec9abf5b869f49e082ab82e7/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_meta/protocol.lua#L2436) and [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/a4006360f1d43211ec9abf5b869f49e082ab82e7/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_meta/protocol.lua#L2449)) and `runtime/lua/vim/lsp/rpc.lua`.\n\nI'd like to suggest that the type annotations of these fields/parameters should be updated from `string` to the appropriate `vim.lsp.protocol.Method` alias. I believe this also aligns with @lewis6991's PR (#33509):\n> These types are then used instead of string where appropriate.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBy annotating `ctx.method` as `vim.lsp.protocol.Method`, it'd be much easier to work with the method names and would help users migrate from the enum.\n\n<img width=\"961\" height=\"254\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7b9c0297-c4d4-4fbe-98da-5daebef18631\" />",
